SUBSTITUTE FOR
SENATE BILL NO. 559
A bill to amend 2000 PA 489, entitled
"Michigan trust fund act,"
(MCL 12.251 to 12.262) by adding sections 11a and 11b.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 11a. (1) Beginning October 1, 2026, the revenue sharing
2 trust fund is established in the department of treasury. The
3 revenue sharing trust fund consists of 1 or more of the following:
4 (a) Money deposited in the revenue sharing trust fund as
5 required by section 25 of the general sales tax act, 1933 PA 167,
6 MCL 205.75.
7 (b) Donations of money made to the revenue sharing trust fund
8 from any source.
9 (c) Interest and earnings from revenue sharing trust fund
BJH S03312'25 (S-1) z13eyf

2
1 investments.
2 (2) The state treasurer shall direct the investment of the
3 revenue sharing trust fund.
4 (3) Money in the revenue sharing trust fund at the close of a
5 fiscal year remains in the revenue sharing trust fund and does not
6 lapse to the general fund.
7 Sec. 11b. (1) Beginning on October 1, 2026, subject to
8 subsections (6) and (7), and upon appropriation, the state
9 treasurer shall transfer and disburse the money received by the
10 revenue sharing trust fund as follows:
11 (a) To cities, villages, and townships, $299,126,400.00 to be
12 distributed to each city, village, or township, regardless of
13 whether any limitation or eligibility criteria under section 952 of
14 article 5 of 2023 PA 119 were met, in the same proportion of the
15 revenue sharing payment that each was eligible to receive under
16 section 952 of article 5 of 2023 PA 119, rounded to the nearest
17 dollar.
18 (b) To cities, villages, and townships, any remaining amount
19 appropriated to be distributed as follows:
20 (i) One-third as taxable value payments as provided under
21 subsection (2).
22 (ii) One-third as unit type population payments as provided
23 under subsection (3).
24 (iii) One-third as yield equalization payments as provided under
25 subsection (4).
26 (c) To counties, $261,069,700.00 to be distributed to each
27 county, regardless of whether any limitation or eligibility
28 criteria under section 952 or 955 of article 5 of 2023 PA 119 were
29 met, in the same proportion of the revenue sharing payment that
BJH S03312'25 (S-1) z13eyf

3
1 each was eligible to receive under section 955 of article 5 of 2023
2 PA 119, rounded to the nearest dollar.
3 (d) To counties, any remaining amount appropriated as a
4 taxable value payment determined as follows for each county:
5 (i) Determine the per capita taxable value for each county by
6 dividing the taxable value of that county by the population of that
7 county.
8 (ii) Determine the statewide per capita taxable value by
9 dividing the total taxable value of all counties by the total
10 population of all counties.
11 (iii) Determine the per capita taxable value ratio for each
12 county by dividing the statewide per capita taxable value by the
13 per capita taxable value for that county.
14 (iv) Determine the adjusted taxable value population for each
15 county by multiplying the per capita taxable value ratio as
16 determined under subparagraph (iii) for that county by the population
17 of that county.
18 (v) Determine the total statewide adjusted taxable value
19 population, which is the sum of all adjusted taxable value
20 population for all counties.
21 (vi) Determine the taxable value payment rate by dividing the
22 amount to be distributed under this subdivision by the total
23 statewide adjusted taxable value population as determined under
24 subparagraph (v).
25 (vii) Determine the taxable value payment for each county by
26 multiplying the result under subparagraph (vi) by the adjusted
27 taxable value population for that county.
28 (2) A taxable value payment described in subsection (1)(b)(i)
29 to each city, village, and township is determined as follows:
BJH S03312'25 (S-1) z13eyf

4
1 (a) Determine the per capita taxable value for each city,
2 village, and township by dividing the taxable value of that city,
3 village, or township by the population of that city, village, or
4 township.
5 (b) Determine the statewide per capita taxable value by
6 dividing the total taxable value of all cities, villages, and
7 townships by the total population of all cities, villages, and
8 townships.
9 (c) Determine the per capita taxable value ratio for each
10 city, village, and township by dividing the statewide per capita
11 taxable value by the per capita taxable value for that city,
12 village, or township.
13 (d) Determine the adjusted taxable value population for each
14 city, village, and township by multiplying the per capita taxable
15 value ratio as determined under subdivision (c) for that city,
16 village, or township by the population of that city, village, or
17 township.
18 (e) Determine the total statewide adjusted taxable value
19 population, which is the sum of all adjusted taxable value
20 population for all cities, villages, and townships.
21 (f) Determine the taxable value payment rate by dividing the
22 amount to be distributed under this subsection by the total
23 statewide adjusted taxable value population as determined under
24 subdivision (e).
25 (g) Determine the taxable value payment for each city,
26 village, and township by multiplying the result under subdivision
27 (f) by the adjusted taxable value population for that city,
28 village, or township.
29 (3) A unit type population payment as described in subsection
