1 (1)(b)(ii) to each city, village, and township is determined as
2 follows:
3 (a) Determine the unit type population weight factor for each
4 city, village, and township as follows:
5 (i) For a township with a population of 5,000 or less, 1.0.
6 (ii) For a township with a population of more than 5,000 but
7 less than 10,001, 1.2.
8 (iii) Except as otherwise provided in subparagraph (xix), for a
9 township with a population of more than 10,000 but less than
10 20,001, 1.44.
11 (iv) For a township with a population of more than 20,000 but
12 less than 40,001, 4.32.
13 (v) For a township with a population of more than 40,000 but
14 less than 80,001, 5.18.
15 (vi) For a township with a population of more than 80,000,
16 6.22.
17 (vii) For a village with a population of 5,000 or less, 1.5.
18 (viii) For a village with a population of more than 5,000 but
19 less than 10,001, 1.8.
20 (ix) For a village with a population of more than 10,000, 2.16.
21 (x) For a city with a population of 5,000 or less, 2.5.
22 (xi) For a city with a population of more than 5,000 but less
23 than 10,001, 3.0.
24 (xii) For a city with a population of more than 10,000 but less
25 than 20,001, 3.6.
26 (xiii) For a city with a population of more than 20,000 but less
27 than 40,001, 4.32.
28 (xiv) For a city with a population of more than 40,000 but less
