15 (A) Fire services.
16 (B) Police services on a 24-hour basis either through
17 contracting for or directly employing personnel.
18 (C) Water services to 50% or more of the township's residents.
19 (D) Sewer services to 50% or more of the township's residents.
20 (b) Determine the adjusted unit type population for each city,
21 village, and township by multiplying the unit type population
22 weight factor for that city, village, or township as determined
23 under subdivision (a) by the population of the city, village, or
24 township.
25 (c) Determine the total statewide adjusted unit type
26 population, which is the sum of the adjusted unit type population
27 for all cities, villages, and townships.
28 (d) Determine the unit type population payment rate by
29 dividing the amount to be distributed under this subsection by the
BJH S03312'25 (S-1) z13eyf

7
1 total statewide adjusted unit type population as determined under
2 subdivision (c).
3 (e) Determine the unit type population payment for each city,
4 village, and township by multiplying the result under subdivision
5 (d) by the adjusted unit type population for that city, village, or
6 township.
7 (4) A yield equalization payment described in subsection
8 (1)(b)(iii) to each city, village, or township must be in an amount
9 sufficient to provide the guaranteed tax base for a local tax
10 effort, but not to exceed 0.02, and is determined as follows:
11 (a) The guaranteed tax base is the maximum combined state and
12 local per capita taxable value that can be guaranteed in a state
13 fiscal year to each city, village, and township for a local tax
14 effort, not to exceed 0.02, if an amount equal to the amount
15 described in subsection (1)(b)(iii) is distributed to cities,
16 villages, and townships whose per capita taxable value is below the
17 guaranteed tax base.
18 (b) The full yield equalization payment to each city, village,
19 and township is the product of the amounts determined under
20 subparagraphs (i) and (ii):
21 (i) An amount greater than zero that is equal to the difference
22 between the guaranteed tax base determined in subdivision (a) and
23 the per capita taxable value of the city, village, or township.
24 (ii) The local tax effort of the city, village, or township,
25 not to exceed 0.02, multiplied by the population of that city,
26 village, or township.
27 (5) For purposes of determining distributions described in
28 subsection (1)(a), any city, village, or township that completely
29 merges with another city, village, or township is a single entity,
BJH S03312'25 (S-1) z13eyf

8
1 so that when determining the distribution the combined single
2 entity is to receive under subsection (1)(a), the city, village,
3 and township revenue sharing amount that each of the merging local
4 units of government was eligible to receive under section 952 of
5 article 5 of 2023 PA 119 is summed.
6 (6) If the balance in the revenue sharing trust fund is less
7 than the amount appropriated, payments made under subsection (1)(b)
8 and (d) must be prorated to reflect the remaining money in the
9 revenue sharing trust fund after distributions made under
10 subsection (1)(a) and (c).
11 (7) If a city, village, township, or county is eligible to
12 receive a distribution under subsection (1), the distribution must
13 be made on the last business day of October, December, February,
14 April, June, or August, as applicable.
15 (8) Money in the revenue sharing trust fund must not be
16 transferred, expended, withdrawn, or otherwise disbursed from the
17 revenue sharing trust fund except as authorized in this section.
18 (9) Payments distributed under this section may be withheld in
19 accordance with sections 17a and 21 of the Glenn Steil state
20 revenue sharing act of 1971, 1971 PA 140, MCL 141.917a and 141.921.
21 (10) For each state fiscal period that begins after September
22 30, 2027, the governor and the state budget director shall include
23 in the annual budget for that fiscal period submitted to the
24 legislature under section 18 of article V of the state constitution
25 of 1963 an appropriation directing the state treasurer to transfer
26 and disburse money from the revenue sharing trust fund as provided
27 in this section.
28 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
29 unless all of the following bills of the 103rd Legislature are
